description: A new module has been inserted into the system.
objects.test: $SNMPTRAPCMD VALERE-DC-POWER-MIB::vpwrTrapModuleInserted VALERE-DC-POWER-MIB::vpwrTrapsMsgString s EXAMPLE VALERE-DC-POWER-MIB::vpwrBayIndex i 9999 VALERE-DC-POWER-MIB::vpwrModuleIndex i 9999

description: Place holder for trap notification message string
variables.name: VALERE-DC-POWER-MIB::vpwrTrapsMsgString

description: Identifies Bay number that this module belongs to.
The possible values are 1 through 16 limited by vpwrSystemShelfCapacity.
variables.name: VALERE-DC-POWER-MIB::vpwrBayIndex

description: This object identifies the module by its position in the shelf.
Module numbering is left to right starting with module 1. So, the
module in the first slot has an index of 1, the next module is 2 and
so on.
variables.name: VALERE-DC-POWER-MIB::vpwrModuleIndex

description: A module has been removed from the system.
